   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE A VIEW OF GOD'S ECONOMY FROM THE NEW TESTAMENT REVELATION 1 Scripture Reading: Eph 3:2-11; 1:9-11 OUTLINE God becoming flesh to bring Himself into man John 1:14: Becoming a God-man.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>To be experienced by man as grace and reality.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>This God-man living a human life on earth: Living and expressing God in the human life John 6:57a; Acts 10:38.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Experiencing everything of the human life to be qualified as the Captain of salvation and our High Priest Heb 2:10, 17-18.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>This God-man, in the human flesh, accomplishing the all-inclusive death on the cross: A death which redeemed the sinners Col 1:20-22.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>A death which released the divine life John 12:24.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>A death which produced the Body of Christ John 12:24.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>A death which created the new man Eph 2:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>A death which terminated the old creation Rom 6:6.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>A death which destroyed Satan Heb 2:14.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>A death which judged the satanic world of darkness John 12:31.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>This God-man entering into resurrection: Being begotten as the firstborn Son of God, having both divinity and humanity Acts 13:33.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Regenerating the many sons of God, who constitute the church, the Body of Christ 1 Pet 1:3; Heb 2:10, 12.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Becoming the life-giving Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>This God-man, in His resurrection, breathing Himself as the Spirit into His disciples John 20:22: To be their life and content Col 3:4.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To be with them forever John 14:20.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To live together with them John 14:19; Gal 2:20b.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>This God-man, having died and resurrected, ascending to the heavens Eph 4:8-12: Bringing with Him the captives whom He took captive out of the hands of Satan.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Presenting these captives to God.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>God giving these captives as gifts to Him, the ascended Head.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>He, in the position of His ascension, giving these gifts to the church to build up the Body.</S>
   </TEXT>
